==English==
===Noun===
'''bitty box'''
# A [[feeble]] [[personal computer]].

===Usage note===
Bitty box is the traditional pejorative term for "a computer sufficiently small, primitive, or incapable so as to cause a [[hacker]] acute [[claustrophobia]] at the thought of [[w:software development|developing software]] on or for it". The term is especially used of small, obsolescent, single-tasking-only personal computers, but the term is a general pejorative opposite of "real computer".

:''Based on the [http://foldoc.doc.ic.ac.uk/foldoc/foldoc.cgi?query=bitty+box&action=Search entry] in [[FOLDOC]]''.

